The President's Council on Jobs and Competitiveness will hold a Listening and Action Session in Portland, Oregon to discuss the engineering shortage in America and its impact on job creation and innovation. The session will include senior Administration officials, business leaders, and Deans from engineering schools. People can participate by submitting questions and comments in advance, watching the live event online, and engaging on Twitter using the hashtag #jobscouncil. These sessions are part of a series taking place around the country to gather new voices and inform the Council's work and recommendations. The Council's core mission is to promote growth by investing in American businesses, educating and training workers, and attracting jobs and businesses to the United States.